title: Lady Hounds lose season finale
text:
PHOTO BY BILL SLATTERY Ocker 
Senior Kaila Ocker gave the Greyhounds a lead with a goal in the 28th minute Monday. Posted: Friday, October 23, 2015 6:00 am Lady Hounds lose season finale 0 comments 
The Shippensburg girl’s soccer team jumped out to an early lead behind a first half goal from senior Kaila Ocker, but the visiting East Pennsboro Panthers responded with four second half tallies to defeat the Greyhounds 4-1 in their season finale Monday. 
Ocker broke through for the Hounds in the 19th minute with a goal assisted by teammate Sarah Strohm.
